JAX-WS is JAVA Api for XML Based Services
Like Every other JAVA EE Standard Comprises of Specification and API

Specification: Rules and Guidelines.
These Guidelines help webservices engine to implement the JAX-WS Standard.

API- has Annotaions

Core Important Annotations:
In Package javax.jws:

@WebService
public class OrderService{
    // TO make this as webservice Class we use @WebService Annotaion.
}

@WebMethod
@WebResult(name="order") Order getOrder(@WebParam(name="orderId") Long orderId){

}

@WebFault
MyException extends Exception{

}

SOAP Binding - Binding Controls how the SOAP message gets Generated when it goes on Apache CXF etc.

@SOAPBinding -> By Default it document/literal


@RequestWrapper  --> Allows us to Wrap the Request. It is very Rarely Used. 
@ResponseWrapper --> Allows us to Wrap the Response. It is very rarely Used.



===========================================================================================
JAXB - JAVA Architecture for XML Binding.
It provides an easy way to MAP java Classes and XML Schema hinding the complexity of XML


XML Schema <---------------> JAVA Object 

Like :
JAVA <-----------> Hibernate <------------> SQL

JAVA <-----------> JAXB <------------> XML

the JAXB api provide 3 tools:

1. XJC --> XML Schema Compiler tools. this is used in top down approach

    XML Schema ------> JAVA Classes

2. SCHEMAGEN tool. this is used in bottom up API

    JAVA Classes -------> XML Schema

XJC and SCHEMAGEN are used in Compile time

3. RUNTIME API:  Does Marshalling and Unmarshalling etc.

    JAVA Object <--------------> XML



Runtime API:
1. Marshall
2. UNMarshall
3. Annotation